                            <comment id="83537" author="utopiabound" created="Thu, 8 May 2014 17:05:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tracing back through test results, this regression seems to have been introduced around Apr 22, 2014.  While the instance with the earliest parent commit I can find is for &quot;5565877 &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3953&quot; title=&quot;lustre build system improvments&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3953&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3953&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; build: cache the results of configure between runs&quot; I suspect this was introduced by that commit&apos;s parent &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7157&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;72accbe&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2600&quot; title=&quot;lustre metadata performance is very slow on zfs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2600&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2600&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; osd-zfs: batched object accounting&quot; which adjusts object accounting in osd-zfs but never seems to run review-zfs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
